inputs.text: (Comic Book Style), (Vibrant Colors),Moebius Style:0.5,Frank Mille r0:5, <lora:realism_lora_comfy_converted.safetensors:1>, high detail, fantasy concept art, 4K, cinematic lighting, The air hangs thick with the bitter residue of forgotten things – a viscous, lavender-scented nightmare of clockwork echoes suspended in a purple tide. I stand within a cavern where time itself seems to weep, confronted by an endless array of frozen moments, each a shattered testament to lives discarded and skills lost. At the heart of this desolate display, a chronometer ticks with excruciating slowness, a relentless reminder of what’s been stolen. The ache within me isn’t sadness, not precisely. It’s a cold, insistent demand for explanation, a pressure to justify the darkness I carry, a need to dismantle the illusion of beauty before it consumes everything
